Rating: 3.0 -------------------------------------------------- === Purchase Information === Product Title: Magic Collection 3.5 Inch Wide Band Bonnet Elastic Band Black Review Date: 2020/11/01 Store: Magic Collection Average Rating: 4.5 Product Details: {'Color': 'Black', 'Age Range (Description)': 'Adult', 'Number of Items': '1', 'Brand': 'Magic Collection', 'Size': '3.5 Inch (Pack of 1)', 'Is Discontinued By Manufacturer': 'No', 'Package Dimensions': '8.39 x 4.88 x 0.59 inches; 1.59 Ounces', 'Item model number': 'SG_B07345F1BX_US', 'UPC': '636227221951'} Review Text: ☆Make SURE you wash this before wearing it. I did not and there were huge dye stains on my pillows. I ended up washing it... there was so much dye in the sink..the water was darker than this... like, Black when I started washing it. I was running water the whole time I was washing it so the water looks like a light purple but it didn.t start that way, the water was nearly jet black at first.
With that said,..I like the band around it..it.s big and spacious as well.

Update...i.ve had to wash it again and again as the stains were still getting on my white pillowcases. The dye for this thing is really strong as it doesn't wash out easily. It can.t be all that safe having that dye seep into your scalp which, seeps into your body/system.
I don.t sleep in it anymore...I just wear it during the day at home when I want my hair out of the way. I ended up buying a white one and that 1 works better for me. Review Title: Wash It Before Wearing! Rating: 4.0 --------------------------------------------------

SUMMARY:  
The purchase history reveals a consumer with a strong preference for quality makeup and hair care products, favoring items that are durable, effective, and stylish. Consistently high ratings (often 5.0) indicate overall satisfaction, particularly for products like makeup brushes and edge control, which perform well and are perceived as great value for the price. The buyer also shows appreciation for aesthetic details, often opting for stylish designs like silver and gold finishes.

Themes in product use showcase a dual focus: everyday makeup application and hair styling for personal care. There’s a preference for tools that ensure longevity and reliability, as indicated by long-term use of brushes that retain their shape and prevent shedding. However, there is also some price sensitivity; the consumer enjoys finding good deals, as evidenced by favorable comments on affordability.

Quality preferences highlight a penchant for user-friendly products, although there are gaps in satisfaction, particularly with eyebrow products characterized by their complexity of use—suggesting a desire for straightforward applications. Lastly, the consumer exhibits a trial-and-error approach with hair accessories, seeking types that align with personal taste, denoting a nuanced preference for fit and functionality.

Overall, the individual seeks high-quality, stylish products that blend functionality with affordability, demonstrating a keen attention to both performance and aesthetic appeal.
